# Remote File Explorer (SSH + Terminal)
This is a lightweight remote file explorer with SSH connection functionality built using Python and Tkinter.

## Features
- Simple UI for SSH connection
- Launches a GNOME terminal using `sshpass` for auto-login
- Secure password input field
- Splash-style window

## Requirements
- Python 3
- `tkinter`
- `sshpass`
- GNOME Terminal

## Installation
Clone the repository:
`git clone https://github.com/yourusername/remote-ssh.git`
`cd remote-ssh`

## Running
Change Directory to remote-ssh:
`cd /path/to/remote-ssh`
Then:
`python3 app.py`
